description: {"blocks":[{"key":"d468e","text":"Background: Early interventions are recognised as key to improving life chances for children and reducing","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8rj0","text":"inequalities in health and well-being, however there is a paucity of high quality research into the effectiveness of","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d554b","text":"interventions to address childhood health and development outcomes. Planning and implementing standalone","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cuvkm","text":"RCTs for multiple, individual interventions would be slow, cumbersome and expensive. This paper describes the","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"edgct","text":"protocol for an innovative experimental birth cohort: Born in Bradford’s Better Start (BiBBS) that will simultaneously","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2hh3s","text":"evaluate the impact of multiple early life interventions using efficient study designs. Better Start Bradford (BSB) has","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4u6ir","text":"been allocated £49 million from the Big Lottery Fund to implement 22 interventions to improve outcomes for","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4dc4u","text":"children aged 0–3 in three key areas: social and emotional development; communication and language","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"k0p4","text":"development; and nutrition and obesity. The interventions will be implemented in three deprived and ethnically","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4atog","text":"diverse inner city areas of Bradford.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aei5n","text":"Method: The BiBBS study aims to recruit 5000 babies, their mothers and their mothers’ partners over 5 years from","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6r8ql","text":"January 2016-December 2020. Demographic and socioeconomic information, physical and mental health, lifestyle","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b81p2","text":"factors and biological samples will be collected during pregnancy. Parents and children will be linked to their","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9sruu","text":"routine health and local authority (including education) data throughout the children’s lives. Their participation in","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"22lba","text":"BSB interventions will also be tracked. BiBBS will test interventions using the Trials within Cohorts (TwiCs) approach","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"728ed","text":"and other quasi-experimental designs where TwiCs are neither feasible nor ethical, to evaluate these early life","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eh5s5","text":"interventions. The effects of single interventions, and the cumulative effects of stacked (multiple) interventions on","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"csmds","text":"health and social outcomes during the critical early years will be measured.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2jjkc","text":"Discussion: The focus of the BiBBS cohort is on intervention impact rather than observation. As far as we are aware","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d3jqg","text":"BiBBS is the world’s first such experimental birth cohort study. While some risk factors for adverse health and social","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bejre","text":"outcomes are increasingly well described, the solutions to tackling them remain elusive. The novel design of BiBBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5r6eq","text":"can contribute much needed evidence to inform policy makers and practitioners about effective approaches to","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8kki6","text":"improve health and well-being for future generations.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5etfj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
